\displaystyle\int_0^{\theta}\frac{x}{(1-x^2)(1-x)}dx
\theta\in(0,\frac{1}{2})
 \begin{align} & \int_0^{\theta}\frac{x}{(1-x^2)(1-x)}\,dx \\[8pt] = & \int_0^{\theta}\frac{x}{(1-x)(1+x)(1-x)}\,dx \\[8pt] = & \int_0^{\theta}\frac{1}{(1-x)^2}\frac{x}{1+x}dx \\[8pt] = & \int_0^{\theta}\frac{1}{(1-x)^2}\Big(1-\frac{1}{1+x}\Big) \, dx \\[8pt] = & \int_0^{\theta}\frac{1}{(1-x)^2}-\displaystyle\int_0^{\theta}\frac{1}{(1-x^2)(1-x)} \, dx \end{align} 
\begin{align} \displaystyle\int_0^{\theta}\frac{x}{(1-x^2)(1-x)}dx & = \int_0^\theta \frac x{(1-x)(1+x)(1 - x)} \,dx \\ \\ & = \int_0^\theta \frac x{(1+x)(1-x)^2}dx \\ \\ & = \int_0^\theta \left[ \frac A{1+x} + \frac B{1-x} + \frac C{(1-x)^2}\right]dx\end{align}
\frac{x}{(1-x)^2(1+x)}=\frac{1}{4(x-1)}-\frac{1}{4(x+1)}+\frac{1}{2(x-1)^2}
